features: ★【Real-time Positioning and Accurate Positioning】: Our 4G TKSTAR TK905 GPS tracker can real-time locate and monitor any remote targets by SMS, APP and Website. It adopts the most advanced technology of GPS and AGPS dual positioning, positioning accuracy up to 5 meters.

★【Electronic Fence (Geo-Fence)】: Setting up one or more geo-fence for the tracker device to get its movements within the district. The gps car locator will send a alarm to APP or send a message to the authorized number when it goes out of or get in the district.

★【No Installation Required】: Built in 5pcs strong magnets, our magnetic vehicle gps tracker can be installed on any iron surface in one second. Widely used for tracking Cars, Motorcycles, bikes, Trucks, Fleet Management and Boats.

★【Energy Saving and Impermeability IP65】: Standby 60 days with built-in 5000mAh lithium-iron battery. This car locator is the ideal choice if you don't want to charge it too often. IP65 waterproof, dustproof, can work on rainy days but can't be submerged in water.

★【Multifunctional】: SMS/APP/Web real-time tracking our gps trackers; Electronic fence; 90 Days History route playback; Over-speed alarm; Shake alarm; Loosing alarm; Low power alarm; APP/Web tracking platform, etc.
★【SIM card not included】: Works worldwide, requires a local SIM card with data traffic plan to work. If worked with Speedtalk SIM card whose monthly fee is only $5 in the US.

Specifications: Network: 4G LTE/GSM/GPRS GPS accuracy: 16-32ft/5-10m Input: 5V-1A Output: 110-220V Battery: 3.7V 5000mAh lithium rechargeable battery Standby time: 50 days Dimensions: 90 x 72 x 22mm Weight: 5.9oz/168g

Vibration, SMS, call can wake up the tracker.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far so good! Everything I was looking for!
reviews.reviewText: Got this tracker for a car that I'm putting in storage so long life battery was a important consideration. Other consideration is that unlike other GPS trackers, there's no hidden contracts and you can use your own SIM card.Battery; It's been 4 days and down to 86% battery life but now I just put it in Sleep mode and will see if that extends it.Set up / features:Very easy to set up, documents are not in perfect english but easy to understand. Love the fact that there's a lot of built in features such as the shock alarm, speed control, geo fencing, sleep mode, the real time tracking and playback online (web or mobile app), I got the speedtalk sim card, which is cheap but I think I probably will end up switching to 1nce.com since that has global coverage and more than enough data / sms I need.Only con is that the device is rather large (large as 3 iphone stacked together) and not super easy to hide on a car - it will be spotted if people look hard enough. But the tradeoff is longer battery life, so you just need to decide.Update ; it's been 32 days and battery is only down to 32%. The key is to put sleep shock and speed settings. Every time you ping it with a text message it has to power up and you lose 1-2% battery. But in sleep mode, it draws very little battery.Definitely recommend if you are looking for something with long battery life. Only drawback is the size

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The magnet is very weak. I wanted to put this in an inconspicuous place on my motorcycle and now I can’t because the magnet falls off during rides! Looking to return the product. If you make a product that will go on an automobile or motorcycle for external use, you should make it so it can take the elements and bumps in the road , so it doesn’t fall off and is a complete waste of money. Please update and make magnet stronger.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not Impressed as of yet.
reviews.reviewText: Well so far I'm not impressed. Purchased the 3G version of the tracker. I can only partially set up tracker thru SMS. I cannot get the tracker to talk to the app or to the website for tracking. I have tried to set the APN (access point name) multiple times with not luck. I am using a speedtalkmobile 2/3/4G LTE sim card as recommended. The directions provided in the box are terrible. Been using the WWW and YouTube to try to figure this out. If I finally figure this thing out I will update. If not its going back!Update: Tracker is getting returned as there are no 2G/3G service providers. TKSTAR recommended getting a Speedtalkmobile sim card. Well Speed talk uses T-mobile and T- mobile no longer supports 2/3G devices. Going to look for a 4g/LTE tracker.
Cathy was a great help on setting up my account for multiple devices and answering a few questions that I had. Would definitely recommend buying from them for their quick service. Thank you Cathy.
